        <dt>Hershey's Perfect Hot Chocolate </dt>
        <dd>
        <p>2 tablespoons sugar</p><p>2 to 3 teaspoons Hershey's Cocoa</p><p>Dash salt</p><p>1 cup milk</p><p>Â¼Â teaspoon vanilla extract</p><p>Mix sugar, cocoa and salt in large mug.</p><p>Heat milk in microwave at HighÂ (100 percent) 1Â½ minutes or until hot.</p><p>Gradually add hot milk to cocoa mixture in mug, stirring until well blended.</p><p>Stir in vanilla. Makes 1 serving.</p><p>Variations:</p><p><strong>Rich and Adult</strong>: Increase cocoa to 2 tablespoons; follow recipe above.</p><p><strong>Lower fat</strong>: Use nonfat milk; follow recipe above.</p><p><strong>Sugar free</strong>: Omit sugar. Combine cocoa and salt. Proceed as above, using nonfat milk. Stir in vanilla and sugar substitute with sweetening equivalent of 2 tablespoons sugar.</p>
        </dd>
