        <div class="text">
        
              <h4 class="title"><a href="/news/local/burlington_county_times_news/burlington-county-freeholders/youtube_ab254dad-c8a1-5f68-aeff-f76bb169d1ad.html">Burlington County Freeholders 2013 <span class="more">read more</span></a></h4>  
        <div class="description video-text">
        
      The Burlington County Board of Chosen Freeholders held its annual organization meeting for 2013 on Jan. 1 at the Olde Historic Court House in Mount Holly. Democrats Aimee Belgard and Joanne Schwartz were sworn into office by Cory Booker, mayor of the City of Newark. Freeholder Joe Donnelly was selected the board's director, and Freeholder Leah Arter is deputy director. The board also recognized first responders who came to the aid of others during Superstorm Sandy and its aftermath.</div>
